content.description: Start on the left side of the boulder with a jug, traverse right, and use a two finger crimp to enter Schisthead, and top out the same. Adds a bit of difficulty.
content.protection: 1 well-placed pad for the lunge to the lip, or just throw down 2
content.location: Left side of the Schisthead Boulder

content.description: Climb the center of the overhang face with a good reach to a hidden jug to finish this one out. For added fun, start on the left side of the face and climb right to the top out; adds a grade of difficulty. V2 without variation, V3 with.
content.protection: One pad will suffice. The landing is flat and forgiving.
content.location: As you stand before Heel Hook Rock, close your eyes and do a 180. Open your eyes and you will see another rock to climb.

content.description: Locate the short uphill side of the boulder and climb the wavy slab over a slanted landing.
content.location: Directly across the hiking path from No Pitons here, on the water side, there is a faint trail that ends at Oceanfront and The Ripple Effect. Ripple Effect is on the left if facing the water.

content.description: Climb the right side of the overhang. Lots of variations and traversing can be done from this point to up the ante to around V1. Great warm-up.
content.location: As you stand before Heel Hook Rock, close your eyes and do a 180. Open your eyes and you will see another rock to climb.

content.description: Traverse in either direction on the riverside lip of this boulder.
content.location: Directly across the hiking path from No Pitons here, on the water side, there is a faint trail that ends at Oceanfront and The Ripple Effect. Oceanfront is on the right if facing the water.

content.description: Find your way up the widening crack on this smallish boulder. A great way to learn how to play around on cracks in a safe manner.
content.location: Following the defined path beyond Heel Hook Rock, this will appear on your right not 10 yards after leaving Heel Hook. Look for the crack on the rock.

content.description: Traverse the low lip climbing up and right on a handful (pun intended) of fun slopers.
content.location: Directly across the hiking path from No Pitons here, on the water side, there is a faint trail that ends at Oceanfront and The Ripple Effect. Oceanfront is on the right if facing the water. Just below the Oceanfront boulder is where Joel's Traverse can be found.

content.description: Match on the undercling with a foot on the big ledge found climber's right of Chicken Man. Reach for the crimp just above and go...not as easy as it sounds.
A baby boulder offering a bagillion variations for a perfect means to warm up on easier lines.
content.location: Continue to walk beyond Hate Rock on the path, passing a picnic table. The rock will be on your right.

content.description: From the edge of the flat rock, jump to two, high opposing slopers finishing straight up with a crimper and a rather difficult mantel.
content.location: From Joel's Traverse, Chicken Man can be found directly behind and closer to the water on a semi-hidden boulder.

content.description: A burly one-mover that doesn't see much attention. Start with both hands on the crimper, toss up to the sloper and try to find the final jug.
content.protection: toss a good pad down, you are going to need it
content.location: Walk about 20 meters beyond Devonian and follow a small side trail to the summit of this boulder.

content.description: Climber's right of No Pitons Here; make your way up some rather fun bubbles and grooves.
content.location: Following the defined path beyond Heel Hook Rock, this will appear on your right not 10 yards after leaving Heel Hook. Look for the crack on the rock; Bubbles is the line to the right of the crack.

content.description: Hop to the sloper on the left center of the face. Using the other sloper to its right, mantel up this excellent route to a rewarding finish. Short but sweet. For added enjoyment, start with your left on a tiny crimp.
content.location: Following the defined path beyond Heel Hook Rock, continue beyond a bench that will appear on your right. 10 or so yards beyond the bench will be a 7ish foot tall rock.
